posts.name: Ari Meles-Braverman
posts.cooked:
Makers Assemble 5951 also has something similar.  

We are almost finished with our teleop code! Over the week, we mainly worked on several automations.  

Auto Reef Scoring  
Early in the season, we decided to take as much workload off the driver as possible. This led us to develop an almost fully automatic scoring system that requires the driver to simply hold the scoring button without any additional input.  

This is the complete automation:  
• Determine the target reef face based on distance, heading, and movement direction.  
• Calculate the optimal path to the target.  
• Execute autonomous movements to reach the target while avoiding obstacles.  
• Provide feedback to the driver about the system’s performance.  

We’re working now on making it more consistent and reliable, with the hopes of having it ready for Israel District 4 (more details to come soon on our Open Alliance thread).

posts.name: Dan
posts.cooked:
We have an algae shooter that worked mechanically well. When the power was set just right to barely clear the barge, minor bouncing wasn’t a major issue. However, it was more likely to happen during real matches against actual barges compared to the practice version.

Despite its effectiveness, we didn’t use the algae shooter quickly. We rarely utilized it in official matches except for this semifinal game, which gives a good example of how we constructed it.
